comment: Lopez (NYK) and Mahinmi (IND) engage for the loose ball.
Turner (IND) and Seraphin (NYK) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Afflalo (NYK) sets the screen on Hill (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Hill (IND) pushes Afflalo (NYK) after he sets a screen.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Afflalo (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Seraphin (NYK) makes contact with Mahinmi's (IND) body that affects his dunk attempt.
Vujacic (NYK) and Seraphin (NYK) maintain legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Ellis (IND) prior to Seraphin cleanly blocking the driving layup attempt.
Mahinmi (IND) continues moving and extends his hip as he sets the screen on Afflalo (NYK) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Seraphin (NYK) sets the screen on George (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lopez (NYK) sets the screen on Hill (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RATR shows that Turner (IND) and Mahinmi (IND) maintain legal guarding position as they contest Vujacic's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Vujacic initiates any leg contact on the play.
Galloway (NYK) commits a take foul on Ellis (IND).

Referees initiated a replay review to confirm that Afflalo (NYK) was behind the 3-point line on his field goal. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined he had stepped OOB before the attempt and IND was awarded possession.
Hill (IND) legally contests Afflalo's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vujacic (NYK) commits a take foul on Hill (IND).
